parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat track can cause the seat to recline or move unexpectedly, leading to loss of control while driving, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The seat track breaks without warning
the seat reclines to the rear of the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat frame can cause the seat to collapse or become unstable, leading to loss of control while driving, which can result in accidents.
The failure of the motorized driver's seat can cause the seat to malfunction, leading to discomfort, distraction, or loss of control while driving, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: the seat is experiencing metal fatigue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear hatch latch can cause the hatch to open unexpectedly while driving, leading to loss of cargo, distraction, and increased risk of accidents. In severe cases, it can also lead to ejection of occupants in the event of a rollover.
symptoms: The rear hatch comes open while driving
the rear hatch will not latch properly
the rear hatch releases while parked
the rear hatch latch disengages while driving
the rear hatch opens on its own.
